    "One suggested that stress from these events would reduce the incentives to screening, while the other suggested that witnessing somebody's death could incline a person to take care of their health in the face of the risk of possible mortality.",
    "For example, death of a family member from cancer could signal to a patient that they might have an increased risk.",
    "Our study seems to differentially confirm both hypotheses.",
